AUDIO: 'scene. And then it goes through this terrain conditioned texturing component which adds texture to the scene. So for example, it turns this base mesh into something like this. And notice it adds the texture to the scene as well. Next,'

[21:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it also introduces lightweight 3D objects which they call assets. And this includes things like trees and shrubs and it adds them to the scene. So here\'s an example of what an asset would look like. Now afterwards, these assets go'

[22:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'through further refinement. So here it goes through this RGBA texture synthesis which basically adds more details to these assets. So for example it refineses the individual leaves of this plant as well. And that\'s why you get'

[22:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'such detailed looking plants. So after going through this step it would look like this. And finally it goes through this component which adds other dynamic elements such as birds flying in the sky or clouds or you know ripples in the'

